                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18430821-2577-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18430821-2577-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430821-2577-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18430821-cd-310" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430821-2577-offence-1 t18430821-cd-310"></join>12th of August</rs>, 1 handkerchief, value 9<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18430821-name-1804" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1804" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1804" type="surname" value="STEVENSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1804" type="given" value="WILLIAM RUFFELL"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430821-2577-offence-1 t18430821-name-1804"></join>William Ruffell Stevenson</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1805" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1805" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1805" type="surname" value="STEVENSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1805" type="given" value="WILLIAM RUFFELL"></interp>WILLIAM RUFFELL STEVENSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Mr. Russell, a job-master, of Plough-yard, Clapham. On Friday night, the 11th of August, I placed two handkerchiefs and something else on the footboard of a fly in a coach-house in my master's yard—there are large gates, and room for seven or eight carriages to stand—I went to work at half-past six o'clock next morning, and found an old handkerchief which I had left, but I missed the one now produced—I saw it again in possession of the policeman—it is mine—there is about an inch in one corner that has been hemmed, but it is picked out now—I can see the place where it has been hemmed—if it is held up to the light you will see the holes—I will swear to it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1806" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1806" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1806" type="surname" value="FARMER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1806" type="given" value="STEPHEN"></interp>STEPHEN FARMER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V</hi> 154.) On the 12th of August the prisoner passed me in Clapham, about twenty minutes before two o'clock in the morning—I followed him for about 250 yards—when he got to the turning to the back of Mr. Russell's stable I lost sight of him—I afterwards went round and searched, but could not find him—I found the front gates open, which five minutes before I met him were fast.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184308210241"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1807" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1807" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1807" type="surname" value="EASTMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1807" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL EASTMAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V</hi> 132.) I received information from Farmer, and apprehended the prisoner—he had a handkerchief with him like this one, but I could not swear it was this.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1808" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1808" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1808" type="surname" value="EDMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1808" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM EDMAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V</hi> 179.) I received information, went to the station, and took this handkerchief from the prisoner's hat—he said he bought it in the New-cut—one corner of it has been hemmed for about an inch, but has been now unpicked.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I had the handkerchief in my hat when I was taken to the station, and I took it to wash myself with before all the policemen, which I should not have done if I had stolen it.</p>
